<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-355-618  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 355 618.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  April 1990 v27 n4 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NetWorld keynoter deflates networking hype. (Canopus Research Presat NetWorld 90 show)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gitlin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Canopus Research Pres William Zachmann tells NetWorld 90 show(Boston, MA) attendees that there is too much hype about newnetworking technologies, that some networking technologies are notas complex or as useful as previously asserted and that usersshould concentrate on function.andP;  Zachmann believes that the'hottest' technology is analog phone-line fax transmission.andP;  Hebelieves that ISDN will never be widespread, it will take a longtime for fiber optics to replace copper-based networks, digitalPBX will never replace local area networks (LANs), there was nodanger in Ethernet 'collisions' which led to token-ring LANs,network management is not useful when it is intrusive, it wasnever hard to connect microcomputers and mainframes, and it is tooimportant to trust an outside organization to build a firm's LAN.andO;A Novell demonstration is briefly described and several newproducts listed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PresentationsNetworksTrade ShowsIndustry AnalysisAttitudeNetWorld.andO;Person:    Zachmann, William (addresses, essays, lectures).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>